[src:information-geometry/cramér-rao-bound] A more general form of the bound can be obtained by considering a biased estimator $T(X)$ , whose expectation is not $\theta$ but a function of this parameter, say, $\psi (\theta )$ .
[src:information-geometry/cramér-rao-bound] Hence $E\{T(X)\}-\theta =\psi (\theta )-\theta$ is not generally equal to 0.
